The Federal Polytechnic, Bida, is ready to commence degree programmes in management courses, in affiliation with the Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida University, Lapai. The rector of the polytechnic, Dr Abubakar Abdul Dzukogi, hosted a delegation of officials from the IBB University, Lapai, for resource inspection of degree programmes in  Business Administration, Public Administration, Mass Communication and Accounting. The deputy vice-chancellor, Academics, IBB University, Professor Aliyu Mohammed Paiko, who led others into a meeting with the rector, during the resource inspection, said his team was satisfied with the human and material resources available in the polytechnic, particularly the multi-million naira equipment found in Mass Communication studios. “We have a lot of consideration for quality and we value the certificates issued by our university. We have gone round the departments and the school library, and found interesting and standard materials suitable for the degree programs. So, by God’s grace, it is our hope that we won’t have problems approving degree programs for Bidapoly at our level,” the DVC said. The rector of the institution, Dr Abubakar Abdul Dzukogi, who commended the resource inspection team, also said that his administration would leave no stone unturned in a bid to ensure that the affiliated programmes succeed. He described the opportunity as a welcome development since it would bring university education closer to people and equally help in capacity building for staff and nonstaff who are desirous of degree certificates.” “So far, we have received commendations from different stakeholders for introducing degree programmes here since 2018. We started with Engineering and Environmental Sciences, especially in affiliation with the Federal University of Technology, Minna, and today we are talking about new programmes with IBB University.  